@r12f , if you are referring to this lldp change, original test gap was not loaded to 202405. So this PR won't be needed in 202405. But if you are asking if we need this test gap to be filled in 202405, I think it would be good to include into 202405. I will confirm with Zhaohui.

For T0 and T1, I used mellanox testbed to confirm this PR won't be needed. Only reason why this was left out in original PR, was due to testing only conducted in t0 and t1 devices. Thats why I didn't realise loganalyzer was not applied correctly in other DUTs.

@ZhaohuiS, could you share if you think this test gap is required for 202405 or not please?

DHCP ACK packets coming from server to the relay with non-zero UDP checksum is not getting validated by the kernel. Its getting bypassed for the UDP checksum and getting relayed to the DHCP clients to the downstream.
Thereby increasing the TX statistics for the Downstream Interfaces in DHCP-MON. Script is failing, could we remove the testcase of changing UDP checksum.
@yaqiangz Please have a look at this test case for the non-zero UDP checksum.

